LIBREADCONFIG uses Waf,
see http://code.google.com/p/waf/ for details

To configure the library run:

./waf configure

To build the library run:

./waf build

To install the library:

./waf install

By default Waf will try to install the library in /usr/local/lib and the header
file in /usr/local/include. If you want to change installation prefix, run

./waf configure --prefix=YOUR/PATH

To enable HDF5 support use

./waf configure --enable-hdf

To build documentation use

./waf configure --enable-doc

For any additional options that come with Waf distribution, see:

./waf help
